body:
If you can compile obs consider trying this patch i guess and let us know if it works.

```patch
diff --git a/plugins/linux-pipewire/pipewire.c b/plugins/linux-pipewire/pipewire.c
index f203d3e37..aeb230e43 100644
--- a/plugins/linux-pipewire/pipewire.c
+++ b/plugins/linux-pipewire/pipewire.c
@@ -522,7 +522,7 @@ static void init_format_info_sync(obs_pipewire_stream *obs_pw_stream)
 
        enum gs_dmabuf_flags dmabuf_flags;
        uint32_t *drm_formats = NULL;
-       size_t n_drm_formats;
+       size_t n_drm_formats = 0;
 
        bool capabilities_queried = gs_query_dmabuf_capabilities(
                &dmabuf_flags, &drm_formats, &n_drm_formats);
```

Got same issue, trying the patch...

By the way, patch didn't apply, because source file use tabs, but `git diff` expand it into spaces. Also, there are two unnecessary spaces in new lines. I suppose patch should be like:
```diff
diff --git a/plugins/linux-pipewire/pipewire.c b/plugins/linux-pipewire/pipewire.c
index f203d3e37..aeb230e43 100644
--- a/plugins/linux-pipewire/pipewire.c
+++ b/plugins/linux-pipewire/pipewire.c
@@ -522,7 +522,7 @@ static void init_format_info_sync(obs_pipewire_stream *obs_pw_stream)

	enum gs_dmabuf_flags dmabuf_flags;
	uint32_t *drm_formats = NULL;
-	size_t n_drm_formats;
+	size_t n_drm_formats = 0;

	bool capabilities_queried = gs_query_dmabuf_capabilities(
		&dmabuf_flags, &drm_formats, &n_drm_formats);
```

> Well, segfault is gone, but now it returns a black screen, when trying to capture the screen or any window

@RStarik 
I suggest opening a new issue if you are having trouble as this one has been closed as fixed and my problem was indeed fixed.
